[3] Cholera - Angola (Uige, Cabinda provinces)
Date: Fri 9 Mar 2018
Source: Noticias AO Minuto [machine trans. edited]
https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/mundo/970239/surto-de-colera-na-provincia-angolana-ja-afetou-730-pessoas-e-matou-13


An outbreak of cholera in the Angolan province has already affected 730 people and killed 13, and according to a press release sent to Lusa agency, the data refer to the period between the last week of December 2017 and 6 Mar 2018, and in January 2018 alone, a total of 419 cases were reported in the city of Uíge, which resulted in 5 deaths, compared with 209 cases and 2 deaths in February 2018.

In the document, the Angolan Ministry of Health reported that the Inter-ministerial Commission of the Response to Endemic Diseases visited that province in the north of the country to "verify the results of actions and complementary measures" in the fight against the cholera epidemic. The districts most affected by the outbreak, namely, Kakiuia, Ana Candande, Candombe Velho, Candombe Novo and Mbemba Ngango, will be part of the roadmap of the Inter-ministerial Commission, which should also visit the province's drug depot.

In addition to this outbreak in Uíge, cases of cholera in the Angolan province of Cabinda were also confirmed this week, with 1 dead and 13 cases reported, local authorities said. This outbreak is, for now, confined to 3 districts of the city of Cabinda, capital of the province.

In the 2 provinces, there are surveillance teams on the ground working on disinfecting the cacimbas and distributing free tablets for the treatment of water for consumption, also carrying out actions to raise awareness of measures to prevent cholera.

