[4] Cholera - Sudan (Central Darfur)
Date: Fri 9 Mar 2018
Source: Radio Dabanga [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/sudan/suspected-cholera-claims-two-more-lives-central-darfur


The spectre of acute watery diarrhea -- suspected to be cholera -- continues to hang over the villages of Nierteti and the western parts of Jebel Marra in Central Darfur. Two more people have died. Fresh reports to reach Radio Dabanga on Thu 8 Mar 2018 say that 2 people died, and 12 others were infected.

A voluntary work activist told Radio Dabanga that 2 people died, and 4 others were infected in the medical isolation centre of Kuweila on Thu 8 Mar 2018. He explained that the total number of cases held at the centre was 20. The isolation centre of Mara received 6 new cases, making the number of cases held at 9 until Thu 8 Mar 2018. The activist said the isolation centre of Nierteti recorded 1 new case and so did the isolation centre of Korifal, pointing out that the total number of cases held at both centres was 7 until Thu 8 Mar 2018.

According to cases reported to this station, the death toll in Nierteti this year [2018] now amounts to at least 22: 18 people were reported to have died from acute watery diarrhoea in Nierteti in February 2018, and 4 people in March 2018 so far.

Acute watery diarrhea is the term the Sudanese authorities and several international organizations use for the disease, of which the spread turned into epidemic proportions last year [2017]. Using WHO pathology standards, doctors and epidemiologists at the time independently confirmed the cases of diarrhea to be cholera.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Central Darfur State is one of the states of Sudan, and one of 5 comprising the Darfur region. It was created in January 2012 as a result of the ongoing peace process for the wider Darfur region. The state was formed from land that had been part of the states of West Darfur and South Darfur. It can be found on a map in southwest Sudan at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Darfur. - Mod.LL]

